Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.49,0:00:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.41,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.03,0:01:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to the start of the Pacific War,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.85,0:01:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in October 1941,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a conference on the Southern Strategy \Nwas held at the Army War College for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.98,0:01:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the Southern Strategy, \Nthe leading role in capturing the Philippines
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was allocated to the 14th Army under the command \Nof Lieutenant General Homma Masaharu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.27,0:02:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To this end, the 5th Air Group was attached to them. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines_campaign_(1941%E2%80%931942)}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.54,0:02:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But the strategy also had an important problematic point.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.19,0:02:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Namely, the question of whether the U.S. Army in Philippines would choose to fight in the capital, Manila,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.88,0:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or retreat to defend the Bataan Peninsula. {strategy of holing oneself up in a castle (house, building)}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.51,0:02:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The task of the 14th Army is to crush the enemy \Nin the Philippines and flatten his main operational base.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.10,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The main operational base being \Nthe capital of the Philippines, Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.02,0:02:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the 14th Army's main force \Nto land at the Lingayen Gulf 10 day after the war starts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.80,0:02:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and occupy the city of Manila within the next 35 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, according to plan, after completing \Nthe first stage, 48th Division and the 5th Air Group
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are to be diverted for the Java and Malay operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Trouble may arise when that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the goal of the Philippine operation \Nto capture the capital city of Manila, or is it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to deal a devastating blow to the enemy forces? {/damage the troops/manpower}\NPlease clarify that for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, the enemy would be very likely to retreat to the Bataan Peninsula, like during the American-Spanish War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.39,0:03:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If the enemy forces concentrate in the Bataan Peninsula, they'd be difficult to destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.70,0:03:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if the 48th Division and the 5th Air Group
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.06,0:03:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are pulled out to participate in the Java-Malay Offensive, \Nour own ranks would be rather thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bataan Peninsula is a natural fortress. \NWe'd be in trouble if they're all driven to there. {/escape to}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.14,0:03:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should think through \Nhow to fight them in Bataan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.91,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I think the probability of that is too low.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy forces would be mostly made up of locals,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore MacArthur must be considering \Na defensive battle in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.16,0:03:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Philippine Operation \Nis to be followed closely by the capture of Java. {I think he means this by https://jisho.org/search/hikaete}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.74,0:03:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason, we must strive to capture Manila \Nin the shortest time possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to dispatch the 48th Division to Java sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In case the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula, \NI suggest that we carefully smoke them out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.01,0:03:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On November 3rd, draft outline of this operation \Nwas submitted to the Chief of Staff, General Sugiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:53.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC5C9C8&\3c&H222418&}Office of the Chief of Staff {参謀本部総長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First operational goal:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.44,0:04:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,crush the enemy in the Philippines \Nand raze to the ground his main operational base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Second operational goal: in cooperation with the Navy, \Nthe Army must land on Luzon and promptly seize Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't write in any provisions \Nin case the enemy retreats to the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.91,0:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That decision rests entirely \Nwith the commander of the 14th Army. {/the question of how to deal with that situation}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any need to write it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:26.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H171514&\3c&HEAEBE9&}14th Army Strategy Draft {第十四軍作戰要領案}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.09,0:04:34.06,Sign,,0,0,250,,{\fade(300,1500)\bord0\blur1\c&HEFF1F6&\b1}Episode 11 \N{\fs90}The Fall of Bataan and Corregidor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 8th, upon receiving the news \Nof the successful surprise attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the massive 11th Air Fleet's land-based formation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of Zero fighters commenced a surprise attacks on American Air Force bases in the Philippines - Clark Field and Iba.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,About a hundred grounded American aircraft, \Nwaiting for orders, were wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.62,0:04:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Within just a day after the outbreak of the war, \NAmerican Air Force presence in the Philippines was no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequently, the main force, led by the 14th \NArmy Commander, Lieutenant General Homma Masaharu,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.10,0:05:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,formed a large transport fleet of 76 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.98,0:05:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was escorted by the 3rd Fleet \Nunder the command of Vice Admiral Takahashi {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E9%AB%98%E6%A9%8B%E4%BC%8A%E6%9C%9B}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and was heading towards the southern waters \Nin the watertight formation. {pretty literal, https://proverb-encyclopedia.com/mizumomorasanu/}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.07,0:05:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather on the day of landing \Nwould be the decisive factor in its success. {no clue what he means: 上陸の日の天候はどうかなまず上陸成功が第一だ}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine. The troops are in high spirits \Nand are already betting at who'll get to Manila first. {believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The morale is as high as it can get. {/brimming with ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, MacArthur also had plenty of time to bolster \Nhis defenses and is definitely expecting our arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.59,0:05:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bataan is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.05,0:05:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"We'll think about it when we get there"? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.88,0:05:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, if we're quick enough to overwhelm Manila, \Nwe won't give the enemy the time to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.19,0:06:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The 14th Army's main force was split into two groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.38,0:06:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They landed on December 22nd in the Lingayen Gulf \Nand on December 24th in Lamon Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,From south and north, \Nthey launched their march straight to Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Japanese{ army}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.93,0:06:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.51,0:07:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Faced with the thunderous advance of the Japanese army, {/tremendous}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,US Army of Philippines \Ncouldn't put up much of a fight at all. {no clue what he means by "wasn't that enemy": アメリカフィリッピン軍はその敵ではなかった}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{We estimated that }The enemy has no more \Nthan 5 divisions in the Central Region.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of those, 3 already suffered devastating losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the Intel on the enemy forces in Manila?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have the exact Intel yet, but a part of those \Nwas already hit considerably hard at the Agno River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, the enemy is probably planning \Nto hold on to Manila? {to stay on; to remain; to hold out; to hold one's ground}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There are, however, reports of small portions of enemy forces gradually retreating towards the Bataan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.56,0:07:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, they've decided to barricade at the Bataan. {to barricade oneself in; to hold (a fort, etc.); to shut oneself up; to be besieged; to dig in}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese offensive is closing in on Manila \Nfrom the north and south.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.39,0:08:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was now apparent to anyone \Nthat the fall of Manila is but a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.48,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,General Douglas MacArthur, the commander \Nof the United States Army Forces in the Far East
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is now faced with an important strategic decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army advances faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.64,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is covered by a considerable air force \Nand has many tanks and field artillery in his arsenal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.99,0:08:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.95,0:09:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Declare Manila an open city
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.33,0:09:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately evacuate all our troops in the south \Nto the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're enacting War Plan Orange?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.12,0:09:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Move the military headquarters to Corregidor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.06,0:09:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll hold fast to that area \Nuntil the relief army arrives from the mainland. {/homeland}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding fast to the Bataan Peninsula \Nand Corregidor is definitely a viable strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.76,0:09:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if San Fernando, the entrance to the Bataan, \Nis captured first, we'll be cut off from the peninsula. {lit: our retreat would be impossible - he means retreat to bataan}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.94,0:09:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't even let us catch our breath. {lit: they won't forgive/allow us a delay of even one moment}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the evacuation is completed, \Nwe have to hold the Japanese back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. With the honor of the \NUS Army of Philippines at stake, we'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Manila has been declared an open city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.71,0:09:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 6 a.m. on January 1st, General MacArthur \Nordered the destruction of the Calumpit Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire army had to complete the evacuation by then. \NSuch was his order.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:10:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, all the US military facilities in Manila \Nwere burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Open City." What this means is, a cloth was hanged out, \Nindicating that the city is defenseless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All the while the long convoys of trucks, chock-full with soldiers, weapons and ammunition hurriedly passed by. {unsure "alongside what" he means, could be bridge, could be cloth}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:24.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H293852&\3c&HBECAD4&\fs60\bord1\blur1\frz300.8\pos(747,640)}Bataan Peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:24.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H293852&\3c&HBECAD4&\fs70\bord1\blur1\pos(1245,704)}Manila Bay
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:24.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H293852&\3c&HBECAD4&\bord1\blur1\pos(1335,326)}Calumpit
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:24.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H293852&\3c&HBECAD4&\bord1\blur1\frz48.53\pos(1037,226)}Pampanga River
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, as expected, the enemy retreated \Nto the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.78,0:10:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The 48th Division Commander
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,strongly suggests that we hinder the enemy's retreat to Bataan Peninsula, putting Manila off for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A report from the reconnaissance plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{Large formations of }The enemy forces are retreating \Nto the Bataan Peninsula one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're seemingly moving from the direction of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad. Now that it's vacant, \Nrushing to Manila is pointless. {/taking Manila away}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.32,0:10:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the enemy is {still desperately }counterattacking over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.99,0:10:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They may not be necessarily retreating to Bataan. {あっさりとバターン半島へ撤退はしまい - no clue what he means, but judging from next line, gotta be around this}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.34,0:10:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's apparent they're retreating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.36,0:11:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We must blow the Calumpit Bridge to prevent their retreat \Nand defeat them decisively in the Luzon Plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it may be a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.85,0:11:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.12,0:11:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are counting on us to crush the enemy \Nand quickly seize Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.63,0:11:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the 48th Division to crush the enemy at Cabanatuan, \Nthen immediately advance on Manila. {very unsure about this city name}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This moment had been anticipated for a long while. {not sure wat he means: かねて予想されていた時代であった}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General Homma pondered it for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.76,0:11:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but ultimately followed the orders of his superiors \Nto fulfill the soldier's duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As instructed by the Imperial Headquarters, \Nhe headed for Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.31,0:11:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the US Army of Philippines \Nsafely concluded the withdrawal to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.09,0:12:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 2nd, Manila surrendered. \NThe Japanese troops marched through the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.78,0:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This, however, was not the end of the Philippines operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.27,0:12:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the US Army of Philippines managed to barricade itself on the Bataan Peninsula and in Corregidor Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ensuring a complete control over Manila Bay \Nwas seen a stepping stone
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in ensuring unchallenged occupation of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So in order to secure Manila Bay,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:35.96,0:12:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island, \Nguarding the entrance to the bay
